This paper focuses on a data stream management system (DSMS) that is commonly placed on top of a cloud infrastructure to handle fast data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DB (databases), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.SY (systems and control), and cs.NI (networking and internet architecture).
